## âœ… what i did  
-clicked start
-opened the terminal
-ran: 'tmux'
-pressed: 'Ctrl+b+c'
-ran: 'grep -r listen /usr/include'
found out the syscall number for listen is 50
-pressed: 'Ctrl+b+p'
-ran: 'vim bro.s'
-typed: '.intel_syntax noprefix'
        '.global _start'
        '_start:'
        'mov rax, 41'
        'mov rdi, 2'
        'mov rsi, 1'
        'mov rdx, 0'
        'syscall'
        'mov r10, rax'
        'sub rsp, 16'
        'mov r11, 2'
        'mov [rsp], r11w'
        'mov r11, 0x5000'
        'mov [rsp+2], r11w'
        'mov r11, 0x00000000'
        'mov [rsp+4], r11d'
        'mov r11, 0'
        'mov [rsp+8], r11d'
        'mov rax, 49'
        'mov rdi, r10'
        'mov rsi, rsp'
        'mov rdx, 16'
        'syscall'
        'mov rax, 50'
        'mov rdi, r10'
        'mov rsi, 0'
        'syscall'
        'mov rax, 60'
        'mov rdi, 0'
        'syscall'
-ran: 'as -o bro.o bro.s'
-ran: 'ld -o bro bro.o'
-flag popped out

## ğŸ§‘ğŸ¾â€ğŸ« what this challenge teaches u
after create the socket and bind it, u have to make the server able to listen on the port
u can achieve this using the listen syscall which its number is 50
it takes only 2 arguments, the socket file descriptor and the backlog -> number of requests that can be in the queue

